def: A tribe of bivalve mollusks in which the posterior mantleborder is prolonged into two tubes or siphons. Called alsoSiphoniata. See Siphon, 2 (a), and Quahaug.
A kind of cap formerly worn by soldiers; -- called also barretcap. Also, the flat cap worn by Roman Catholic ecclesiastics.
in a convincing manner; in a manner to compel assent.
One who receives the profits, as of an estate.
Having a nucleole, or second inner nucleus.
A race Hindostan, believed to be the original people whooccupied the land before the Hindoo or Aryan invasion.
A cooling periodical wind in the Isle of Cyprus, blowing fromthe northwest from eight o'clock, A. M., to the middle of the day orlater.
A prefix meaning contrary, opposite, in opposition; as,counteract, counterbalance, countercheck. See Counter, adv. & a.
Race; offspring; stock; breed; strain. [Obs.] Chaucer.
A prefix signifying between, among, part.
